Diagnosis.
Body black or dark brown (
Fig. 5
); third antennomere (including annellus) 1.5 × longer than fourth segment (
Fig. 6G
); eye in dorsal view 0.8 × as long as temple; eye in lateral view 1.4 × higher than wide (
Fig. 4I
); frons around antennal sockets rugose, vertex and temple smooth (
Fig. 6I
); face weakly punctate, 2.5 × wider than high, rather convex medially, with a short medio-longitudinal ridge (
Fig. 6J
); clypeus small and semi-ellipitcal, with some punctures and long setae (
Fig. 6J
); precoxal sulcus narrowly crenulated, almost reaching anterior edge of epicnemial area and middle coxa (
Fig. 6C
); notauli sculptured and incomplete, only present anteriorly; medioposterior depression deep and linear, not extending to middle of mesoscutum, mesoscutum smooth, with some long setae along notauli (
Fig. 6D
); surface of propodeum densely reticulate-rugose, with medio-longitudinal carina and several transverse carinae, areola absent posteriorly (
Fig. 6E
); pterostigma wide and elliptical, 4.0 × longer than its maximum width (
Fig. 6A
); hind coxa smooth (
Fig. 6N
); length of first tergite almost equal to its apical width, its surface finely longitudinally striate (
Fig. 6E
), dorsal carinae widely separate medially; setose part of ovipositor sheath 0.88 × as long as fore wing (total visible sheath 0.9 times), and 2.4 × as long as hind tibia (
Fig. 6H
).

Head. Transverse, width of head 2.1 × its lateral length, and 1.4 × wider than mesoscutum (
Fig. 6I
); antenna with 47 antennomere, third antennomere (including annellus) 1.5 × longer than fourth antennomere, length of third, fourth and penultimate antennomere 3.8, 2.5 and 1.7 × their width, respectively (
Fig. 6G
); length of maxillary palp 1.3 × height of head (
Fig. 5
); eye in dorsal view 0.8 × as long as temple; eye in lateral view 1.4 × higher than wide (
Fig. 6I
); frons around antennal sockets rugose, vertex and temple smooth (
Fig. 6I
); OOL:diameter of ocellus:POL= 19:5:7; face weakly punctate, 2.5 × wider than high, rather convex medially, with one short mediolongitudinal ridge (
Fig. 6J
); clypeus small and semi-elliptical, with some punctures and long setae (
Fig. 6J
); mandible enlarged apically, dorsal tooth enlarged, lobe-shaped (
Fig. 6L
), ventral tooth medium-sized and lobeshaped, separate from first tooth (
Fig. 6M
), middle tooth curved and acute, with small incision between first and second tooth (
Fig. 6M
), medial length of mandible 1.4 × its maximum width.

Mesosoma. Length of mesosoma 1.5 × its height (
Fig. 6C
); pronope absent (
Fig. 6I
); medio-anteriorly pronotum widely crenulate, remainder of pronotum smooth; epicnemial area crenulated and rugose; precoxal sulcus narrowly crenulate, almost reaching anterior edge of epicnemial area and middle coxa; pleural sulcus distinct crenulated; episternal scrobe linear and deep; metapleuron densely rugose ventrally, remainder smooth (
Fig. 6C
); notauli sculptured and incomplete, only present anteriorly; medio-posterior depression deep and linear, not extending to middle of mesoscutum, mesoscutum smooth, with some long setae along imaginary course of notauli; scutellar sulcus deep and narrow, with one medio-longitudinal carina, sulcus 5.0 × wider than its maximum length; scutellum smooth (
Fig. 6D
); surface of propodeum densely reticulate-rugose, with medio-longitudinal carina present and several transverse carinae, areola absent posteriorly (
Fig. 6E
).

